com.ethanruffing.preferenceabstraction

Class AutoPreferences

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ethanruffing.preferenceabstraction.AutoPreferences
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IPreferences

    public class AutoPreferences
extends Object
implements IPreferences
    This class provides a layer of abstraction over the possible methods for storing preference data. It will give priority first to a local preferences file, then to such a file in the user's home directory, and finally, to preferences stored in the system preference structure.

    Note: Per convention, preferences are separated by package. Therefore, preferences for multiple classes in the same package will be stored together, and may overwrite one another.

    Note that the only format currently supported for file-based storage is XML.

    Since:
    2016-02-17
    Author:
    Ethan Ruffing
